underlying_goal: To add 95% confidence interval error bars to the plots in a LaTeX research report.
friction_detail: Claude initially added CIs to the text of the report instead of the figures. After clarification, it encountered and fixed a bug in the plotting script where error bar values were negative.
primary_success: Successfully updated a Python plotting script to calculate and display 95% Wilson CI error bars on all figures in the research report.
brief_summary: User wanted 95% CI error bars added to a LaTeX research report. Claude first misunderstood and added CIs to the text, but after the user clarified it should be in figures, Claude modified the plotting script, fixed a calculation bug, regenerated all plots with error bars, and recompiled the final PDF.
